    "date": "2021-08-13T18:09:28Z",
    "text": "Climate Resilient Transportation Infrastructure Study Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Transportation to enter into an agreement with the Transportation Research Board of the National Academies to conduct a study of the actions needed to ensure that federal agencies are taking into account current and future climate conditions in planning, designing, building, operating, maintaining, investing in, and upgrading any federally funded transportation infrastructure investments."
